WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.836
Time to deploy a real app!

00:00:02.836 --> 00:00:05.590
We will go from an empty repo to running

00:00:05.590 --> 00:00:07.426
containers in a few short steps.

00:00:08.288 --> 00:00:10.928
The flow is simple: pick a template, apply

00:00:10.928 --> 00:00:13.488
it to the repo, and run it. The CLI ships

00:00:13.488 --> 00:00:16.288
built-in templates so we never have to write a docker

00:00:16.288 --> 00:00:17.568
-compose from scratch.

00:00:21.038 --> 00:00:23.678
Step one. We will list the available templates

00:00:24.558 --> 00:00:27.118
. Rediacc ships ready-made setups for common apps

00:00:27.118 --> 00:00:29.998
so we do not have to write a docker-compose from scratch.

00:00:31.629 --> 00:00:34.509
The full template catalog. Each one is a tested

00:00:34.509 --> 00:00:36.909
compose plus Rediaccfile pairing.

00:00:40.337 --> 00:00:41.011
Step two.

00:00:41.011 --> 00:00:43.371
Drop the app-postgres template into the repo.

00:00:43.371 --> 00:00:46.068
This copies a tested set of files into

00:00:46.068 --> 00:00:47.416
the repo for us.

00:00:49.666 --> 00:00:50.341
Template applied.

00:00:50.341 --> 00:00:53.038
Let us see what actually landed in the

00:00:53.038 --> 00:00:53.376
repo.

00:00:56.702 --> 00:00:59.331
Let us look at what the template added.

00:00:59.331 --> 00:01:01.960
We connect into the repo and list its

00:01:01.960 --> 00:01:02.288
files.

00:01:02.288 --> 00:01:04.917
There is a Rediaccfile holding the start and

00:01:04.917 --> 00:01:05.575
stop hooks,

00:01:05.575 --> 00:01:07.875
and a docker-compose file describing the containers.

00:01:07.875 --> 00:01:08.532
One note:

00:01:08.532 --> 00:01:11.161
we add a redirect to dev null so

00:01:11.161 --> 00:01:12.804
only the real output shows.

00:01:12.804 --> 00:01:13.461
Without it,

00:01:13.461 --> 00:01:15.762
the connection logs would clutter the screen.

00:01:15.762 --> 00:01:18.390
We will keep doing that for the rest

00:01:18.390 --> 00:01:19.376
of the commands.

00:01:22.126 --> 00:01:23.184
Two files:

00:01:23.184 --> 00:01:25.829
Rediaccfile for the lifecycle hooks,

00:01:25.829 --> 00:01:28.474
and docker-compose.yml for the containers.

00:01:31.814 --> 00:01:33.879
Now bring the repo up.

00:01:33.879 --> 00:01:35.944
The CLI starts the containers,

00:01:35.944 --> 00:01:37.596
mounts the encrypted volume,

00:01:37.596 --> 00:01:40.487
and wires up the isolated Docker daemon.

00:01:43.237 --> 00:01:44.288
Containers running,

00:01:44.288 --> 00:01:45.340
volume mounted,

00:01:45.340 --> 00:01:47.442
isolated Docker daemon up.

00:01:50.766 --> 00:01:52.955
Let us verify what is running.

00:01:52.955 --> 00:01:55.509
Docker ps here lists only this repo's

00:01:55.509 --> 00:01:55.874
containers.

00:01:55.874 --> 00:01:58.428
Other repos on the same server have

00:01:58.428 --> 00:02:00.982
their own daemons and are completely invisible

00:02:00.982 --> 00:02:02.077
from this view.

00:02:03.327 --> 00:02:05.291
Only this repo's containers.

00:02:05.291 --> 00:02:07.256
The isolation is real,

00:02:07.256 --> 00:02:08.238
not configuration.

00:02:09.151 --> 00:02:11.711
And that wraps up your first deploy

00:02:12.191 --> 00:02:14.751
. See you in the next one, where we dig into

00:02:14.751 --> 00:02:16.751
working with the repo itself.
